*edit: both variants sold. 
Got two colored reproductions of this Dungeon Derelict piece. Frame and skull piece is cast in plastic resin and hand painted, background is an edited print from the original black and white painting. The green and purple one has real bars casted into it while the red and yellow has casted plastic bars painted to look metal. About 9x7 $100 each, DM to purchase 💀 
.
.
.
.

First revamped motionette for this year is an abominable snowman/yeti. Took the clothes off of a very thicc Santa and sculpting over the face and feet with air dry clay (which is such a weird consistency and so obnoxious to work with 😅). Once he’s dry he’ll get claws and a paint job, then covered in fur. I can’t wait til he’s done he’s going to be so cute 😭. Basically an arctic Ludo lol 
.
.
.

#abominablesnowman #yeti #motionette #christmasdecor #yuletidebuddies #revamped #dasclay #airdryclay #thiccsanta #wip #processvideo #smallbusiness #creepychristmas

Merry Yuletide and happy holidays! It’s hard to find time to do everything on the list this time of year, but @rob_drokker and I stayed up late to make sure this yeti got some fur to stay warm for the day 😄. I love how this motionette came out I think he’s cute as pie ☺️. Definitely our new tradition to make a new one every year, with plan to have more for sale if you’re into having a festive little guy! I have a new Krampus that didn’t quite get finished in time but he’s still going to come to life! Hope you’re all having a gentle and lovely day whatever you’re doing 💙
.
.
.
.
#abominablesnowman #yeti #motionette #christmasdecor #yuletide #happyholidays #newtradition #unconventionalchristmas #skullcurseproductions

My first velvet painting framed on the wall ✨ based it on an illustration that my grandpa did (second to last slide). He was always an artistic inspiration for me, I don’t have a lot of his art so what I do possess is very special to me. He did some extensive family research and I always loved the Taylor coat of arms he did (last slide). ANYWHO velvet painting is hard 🤣 but I learned a lot I’m excited to do more! I’ve been collecting some cool frames specifically for some new velvet pieces I want to do. 
.
.
.
.
#velvetpainting #velvet #knight #coatofarms #70sinspired #homedecor #ewingtaylor #familyhistory #armour #joust #vintageart

Gargoyle of Notre Dame, Alphaflex acrylic fabric paint on velvet. I thought this frame went particularly well with it 👹 painting is 12x20 and available with frame included, DM to claim. Im having a LOT of fun with the velvet, I’ve got some spicy red velvet ones on deck next 😈.

sick new @lorddying video out now! 🐙🕷️insane creature fx by @smelly.elle @faust.and.company // dir. @zev_deans // dp @unholyroman

Now that the @lorddying video for I AM NOTHING I AM EVERYTHING has been released I wanted to share some behind the scenes shots of the practical fx work @faust.and.company and I got to work on! Such a freaking cool experience and I learned so much from Markus! Directed by @zev_deans and shot by @unholyroamin who are both extremely talented and cool and so much fun to work with.  I’m also the actor in the video and @faust.and.company did a great job doing an impromptu last minute makeup job on me 😄. Hope you all dig the video! 
.
.

Commissioned piece I finished earlier this year for @rankandvilegrind , used as the insert of their latest album WORSHIP, you should check out!! This was the first time I decided to try and tackle a completely digital painting, and there were definite benefits to it, but I found I gotta have hands on paper to really enjoy the process! So maybe never again 😄. Zoom in on this bad boy though I packed a lot of detail in there. Thanks for lookin’!
